The Chairman of Abuja Municipal Area Council (AMAC), Abdullahi Adamu Candido, has declared his intention to seek re-election in 2019. “I will like to respond to your clarion call for me to come out and seek re-election in 2019. I wish to offer myself once again to serve my people in this council as you have demonstrated your trust in me,” he said, during a town hall meeting in Apo yesterday. The town hall meeting was part of events organised to celebrate his two years in office. He said he was seeking re-election in order to complete “the good work we have started in taking this council to its dreamland.” In his remarks, the All Progressives Congress (APC) chairman in AMAC, Abbas Baba, commended Candido for his efforts in delivering the dividends of democracy to the residents. He said the party was proud of his achievements and urged residents to support him in furthering them.